---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Starfield from '@/components/Starfield.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  active="genesis"
  title="Adamant — Genesis"
  description="How Adamant launches: a fixed 100M ADM genesis pool, partitioned 70/30, two ways in, no premine, no foundation allocation."
  ogImage="/genesis-og.png"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden pt-10 md:pt-16 pb-12 md:pb-16">
    <Starfield />
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-[1] glow-pulse" style="background:radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 50% at 75% 40%, rgba(255,125,77,0.08), transparent 65%)"></div>
    <div class="wrap relative z-[3]">
      <div class="grid items-center gap-10 md:gap-14 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr]">
        <div data-reveal>
          <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Genesis · launch mechanism</span>
          <h1 class="mt-6 max-w-[14ch] font-display font-medium leading-[0.98] tracking-[-0.035em]" style="font-size:clamp(40px,5.6vw,84px)">
            <span class="block font-light text-ink-2">A fixed pool.</span>
            <span class="block font-bold text-ember">No private allocation.</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-7 max-w-[44ch] text-[16.5px] leading-[1.7] text-ink-2">
            100M ADM. Burn-to-mint and Node Runner rewards. Five-year launch phase.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="glass rounded-sm flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 md:p-8" data-reveal style="transition-delay:120ms">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-rule pb-3.5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">Pool size</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[26px] font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.03em]">100M<small class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] font-normal tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-3">ADM</small></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-rule pb-3.5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">Path A · burn</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[26px] font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.03em]">70M<small class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] font-normal tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-3">70%</small></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-rule pb-3.5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">Path B · Node Runners</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[26px] font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.03em]">30M<small class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] font-normal tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-3">30%</small></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-rule pb-3.5">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">Time cap</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[26px] font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.03em]">5<small class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] font-normal tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-3">YEARS</small></span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">Founder allocation</span>
            <span class="font-display text-[26px] font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.03em] text-ember">0<small class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] font-normal tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-3">ZERO</small></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Partition donut -->
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="num">§01 / THE POOL</span>
          <h2><span class="light">One hundred million,</span>partitioned at genesis.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="desc">The full supply of ADM is set at genesis and minted only as it's claimed. There is no token that exists before someone earns it through one of the two paths.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.2fr]">
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 400 400" class="max-w-[440px] w-full">
            <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="160" fill="none" stroke="rgba(236,232,223,0.06)" stroke-width="48" />
            <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="160" fill="none" stroke="#ff7d4d" stroke-width="48" stroke-dasharray="703.7 1005.3" stroke-dashoffset="0" transform="rotate(-90 200 200)" />
            <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="160" fill="none" stroke="#7da6ff" stroke-width="48" stroke-dasharray="301.6 1005.3" stroke-dashoffset="-703.7" transform="rotate(-90 200 200)" />
            <text x="200" y="190" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Unbounded" font-weight="500" font-size="42" fill="#ece8df" letter-spacing="-1.5">100M</text>
            <text x="200" y="220" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="11" fill="#5a5d6b" letter-spacing="3">ADM · FIXED</text>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
          <div class="flex gap-5 border-l-2 border-ember pl-6" data-reveal>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="mb-2 flex justify-between font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">
                <span class="text-ember">PATH A · BURN-TO-MINT</span>
                <span class="text-ink-2">70,000,000 ADM</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7] text-ink-2">Anyone who burns BTC, ETH, USDT, or USDC to a verifiable null address can claim ADM at the protocol-defined rate of 20 ADM per USD-equivalent (1 USDT = 1 USDC = 20 ADM; BTC/ETH at USD-equivalent calibrated at protocol design time). Mathematics; no permission needed. Per-address claim caps prevent early concentration.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-5 border-l-2 border-cold pl-6" data-reveal>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="mb-2 flex justify-between font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">
                <span class="text-cold">PATH B · NODE RUNNER REWARDS</span>
                <span class="text-ink-2">30,000,000 ADM</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7] text-ink-2">Earned block-by-block by the <strong class="font-semibold text-ink">Node Runners</strong> (validators in the spec) actually running the chain. The only way to acquire stake from work, not capital. Calibrated to drain over the launch phase — a target of two to three years at single-digit ADM per block.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-5 border-l-2 border-ink-3 pl-6" data-reveal>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="mb-2 flex justify-between font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">
                <span class="text-ink-3">UNCLAIMED · BURNED</span>
                <span class="text-ink-3">DESTROYED AT 5Y</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7] text-ink-2">If the pool isn't exhausted within five years of genesis, the remainder is provably destroyed. The protocol does not retain it. The founders do not retain it. It simply ceases to exist.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Path A cap schedule -->
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="num">§02 / PATH A · CAP SCHEDULE</span>
          <h2><span class="light">Caps that lift</span>over twelve months.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="desc">Per-address claim caps prevent the first hour from being dominated by a few large actors. The cap rises through five phases until it lifts entirely at month twelve.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-rule-2 bg-bg-2/60 backdrop-blur-sm overflow-hidden">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-5 gap-px bg-rule-2">
          {[
            { phase: 'Months 0–1', cap: '1%', desc: 'Tightest cap. The first month is for spreading distribution wide.' },
            { phase: 'Months 1–3', cap: '2%', desc: 'Slight relaxation as participation broadens.' },
            { phase: 'Months 3–6', cap: '4%', desc: 'Mid-launch. More room for committed holders.' },
            { phase: 'Months 6–12', cap: '8%', desc: 'Late launch. Caps still meaningful but minimal.' },
            { phase: 'Month 12+', cap: 'Uncapped', desc: 'Caps lift. Anyone can claim any amount.', em: true },
          ].map((p) => (
            <div class:list={['bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 lg:p-7 flex flex-col gap-4 min-h-[200px] min-w-0 overflow-hidden', p.em && 'bg-bg-3/80']}>
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-3">{p.phase}</span>
              <span
                class:list={[
                  'font-display font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.035em] truncate',
                  p.em ? 'text-ember text-[clamp(28px,3.2vw,38px)]' : 'text-ink text-[clamp(34px,3.6vw,44px)]',
                ]}
              >{p.cap}</span>
              <p class="text-[12.5px] leading-[1.6] text-ink-2 mt-auto">{p.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───────── §03 / POST-LAUNCH ISSUANCE ───────── -->
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="num">§03 / POST-LAUNCH ISSUANCE</span>
          <h2><span class="light">After the launch phase,</span>new ADM goes to those running the chain.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="desc">Once the genesis pool exhausts (or the five-year cap is reached), the protocol transitions to a perpetual issuance schedule. The rate is fixed at genesis and cannot be modified without a hard fork. Issuance flows to Node Runners and their delegators (the substantial majority) and to the Witness compensation pool (a small slice, ~5%) — never to a foundation, never to a treasury, never to the implementers. Provers and service nodes are fee-funded; they receive no issuance.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Issuance schedule grid -->
      <div class="border border-rule-2 bg-bg-2/60 backdrop-blur-sm overflow-hidden">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-px bg-rule-2">
          {[
            { phase: 'Years 1–5', rate: '4%', desc: 'Substantial early rewards to bootstrap a robust Node Runner set.' },
            { phase: 'Years 6–10', rate: '3%', desc: 'Inflation tapers as the chain matures and fee revenue grows.' },
            { phase: 'Years 11–20', rate: '2%', desc: 'Continued tapering toward long-run equilibrium.' },
            { phase: 'Year 21+', rate: '1%', desc: 'Asymptotic floor in perpetuity. Balances against fee burn.', em: true },
          ].map((p) => (
            <div class:list={['bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 lg:p-7 flex flex-col gap-4 min-h-[210px] min-w-0 overflow-hidden', p.em && 'bg-bg-3/80']}>
              <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-3">{p.phase}</span>
              <span
                class:list={[
                  'font-display font-medium leading-none tracking-[-0.035em]',
                  p.em ? 'text-ember text-[clamp(34px,3.6vw,44px)]' : 'text-ink text-[clamp(34px,3.6vw,44px)]',
                ]}
              >{p.rate}<small class="ml-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] font-normal tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-3">/ YEAR</small></span>
              <p class="text-[12.5px] leading-[1.6] text-ink-2 mt-auto">{p.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Where it goes + supply dynamics -->
      <div class="mt-px grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-rule-2 border border-rule-2">
        <article class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9 flex flex-col gap-3.5" data-reveal>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">WHERE ISSUANCE GOES</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">WP §10.3.2</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[26px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.025em]">Node Runners (majority). Witnesses (~5%). Nothing else.</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">Each epoch, the substantial majority of issuance is distributed across the active set in proportion to bonded stake, including delegations; each Node Runner's share is then split between the Node Runner and their delegators per commission rate (typically 5–15%). A small slice flows to the Witness compensation pool, distributed across phone-class participants performing attestation, data-availability sampling, proof verification, and fraud detection. Provers and service nodes earn from transaction fees, not issuance. No portion is reserved for a foundation or development fund.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9 flex flex-col gap-3.5" data-reveal>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">SUPPLY DYNAMICS</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">WP §10.4.4</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[26px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.025em]">Issuance balanced against fee burn.</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">Base fees on every transaction are destroyed via an EIP-1559-style mechanism; tips go to Node Runners. Under typical usage, fee burn approximately equals issuance, producing roughly stable supply. Heavy usage produces net deflation; light usage produces modest inflation.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───────── §04 / GENESIS COHORT ───────── -->
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="num">§04 / GENESIS COHORT</span>
          <h2><span class="light">The first 75 to take a slot,</span>recognised on-chain.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="desc">The chain self-activates the moment 7 Node Runners are simultaneously registered, stake-eligible, and online — no coordination event, no curated recruitment. The first 75 validator addresses to take an active-set slot during the launch period form the <strong class="font-semibold text-ink">genesis cohort</strong> and receive two on-chain artefacts recognising their role in bootstrapping the network. Whitepaper §8.1.9.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-rule-2 border border-rule-2">
        <article class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9 flex flex-col gap-3.5" data-reveal>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">ARTEFACT 01 · MARKER</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">Permanent · non-transferable</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[26px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.025em]">A permanent on-chain marker, bound to the original address.</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">Each of the first 75 addresses is tagged with its cohort position (1–75), the epoch at which the slot was activated, and a cryptographic commitment to chain state at that moment. The marker is non-transferable for the lifetime of the chain. It does not move with slot transfers, cannot be revoked, and survives exit or slashing — it records who was there at activation, not what they did afterwards.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9 flex flex-col gap-3.5" data-reveal>
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">ARTEFACT 02 · GENESIS NFT</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">Tradeable · cultural</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[26px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.025em]">A freely tradeable Genesis NFT, minted at activation.</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">A non-fungible token minted to each genesis cohort address at the moment the slot is taken. The NFT has no protocol-level function — no rights, no privileges, no consensus role; holding it does not make anyone a validator. It exists as a cultural artefact, freely tradeable, that the original cohort can sell, hold, or pass on independent of any decision they later make about the slot itself.</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-px border border-rule-2 border-t-0 bg-bg-2/40 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9" data-reveal>
        <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">WHY BOTH</span>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">WP §8.1.8 · §8.1.9</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-[14.5px] leading-[1.7] text-ink-2">Active-set slots themselves are <strong class="font-medium text-ink">transferable by mutual consent</strong>: a Node Runner may transfer their slot to another address at any time, the protocol is neutral on the economic terms, and there is no counterparty restriction. The launch period rewards registration order and continuity; the long-term composition of the active set reflects the choices of slot holders. The two artefacts split the recognition cleanly. The marker is non-transferable because it records a historical fact about an address — the chain's record of who was there, which is not something anyone can sell. The NFT is transferable because it is a cultural artefact, and cultural artefacts are properly tradeable. Genesis validators who later transfer their slot retain the marker (the chain remembers them) and may keep, sell, or pass on the NFT (the cultural value of having been there). The cohort closes once 75 distinct addresses have been seated; slot 76 onward is an ordinary slot with no marker and no NFT.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stake floors callout -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-rule-2 border border-rule-2" data-reveal>
        <article class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9 flex flex-col gap-3.5">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">TO TAKE A SLOT</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">WP §8.1.4</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[26px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.025em]">Node Runner · 1,000 ADM</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">Each genesis cohort slot requires <strong class="font-semibold text-ink">1,000 ADM bonded stake</strong> at registration to be admitted; transfers also require the buyer to post the current minimum. 28-day unbonding. At 20 ADM per USD-equivalent that's 50 USD-equivalent in burned external value to obtain — the floor is calibrated for residential-fibre accessibility, not VC-grade scarcity. Subject to scheduled re-evaluation at five-year intervals (WP §11.5.4) to prevent token-appreciation-driven exclusion.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm p-7 md:p-9 flex flex-col gap-3.5">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">TO PARTICIPATE WITHOUT A SLOT</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">WP §8.7.2</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[26px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.025em]">Node Watcher · 100 ADM</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">A <strong class="font-semibold text-ink">100 ADM Sybil-resistance stake</strong> registers a phone-class device as a Node Watcher: attests to the recursive proof, samples data availability, verifies on-device, flags fraud. 7-day unbonding; slashable for false attestations corroborated by other watchers. Provers and service nodes are stake-free — anyone with the relevant hardware can begin operating the moment the chain is live. See <a href="/about#participation" class="text-ember underline-offset-4 hover:underline">about §03</a> for the full four-tier breakdown.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───────── §05 / WHAT IS NOT HAPPENING ───────── -->
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="num">§05 / WHAT IS NOT HAPPENING</span>
          <h2><span class="light">Notable absences,</span>by design.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="desc">Most chain launches involve at least some of these. Adamant deliberately involves none. The negative space is the point.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-rule-2 border border-rule-2">
        {[
          ['No premine', 'No tokens exist before genesis. Not even one.'],
          ['No founder allocation', 'The implementers receive no ADM by virtue of having built it.'],
          ['No VC round', 'Nobody has invested cash in exchange for early tokens.'],
          ['No insider sale', 'There is no private round at a discount before public access.'],
          ['No foundation reserve', 'No pool of ADM held back for future protocol development.'],
          ['No vesting cliff', 'Because there is no allocation to vest.'],
          ['No bridge subsidy', 'No marketing fund. No incentive program. No liquidity mining.'],
          ['No retroactive airdrop', 'No reward for past activity on other chains.'],
        ].map(([t, p]) => (
          <div class="bg-bg-2/70 backdrop-blur-sm px-7 md:px-9 py-7 md:py-8 flex items-start gap-5 card-hover" data-reveal>
            <span class="font-mono text-[14px] text-ember leading-none mt-1">×</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-display text-[18px] font-semibold tracking-[-0.018em] mb-1.5">{t}</h4>
              <p class="text-[13.5px] leading-[1.6] text-ink-2">{p}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 text-center border-t border-rule">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 class="mx-auto mb-8 max-w-[26ch] font-display font-medium leading-[1.05] tracking-[-0.035em]" style="font-size:clamp(28px,3.6vw,52px)">
        <span class="block font-light text-ink-2">The full mechanism is in</span>specification §10–11.
      </h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        <a href="/spec" class="btn-link solid">Read the spec <span class="arrow"></span></a>
        <a href="/about" class="btn-link">Plain-English version <span class="arrow"></span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
